        <p>This is a demonstration of a server-based blogging web app that uses Bootstrap, Node, Express, EJS, Express Session, Mongoose and MongoDB Atlas cloud database. It demonstrates backend Create/Read manipulation of a MongoDB Atlas database hosted on AWS. Node server hosting uses Heroku.</p>
        <p>Additional functionality includes subject and author searches, and user signup, login, and authentication functionality.</p>
        <p>The basic functionality is based on Greg Lim's tutorial book "Beginning Node.js, Express, and MongoDB" with customisation and improvements added by myself. </p>
        <p>The presentation is based on the 'Clean Blog' Bootstrap template provided by <a href="https://startbootstrap.com" target="_blank"><strong>startbootstrap.com</strong></a> while images were provided by <a href="https://unsplash.com/" target="_blank"><strong>unsplash.com</strong></a></p>
        <p>Mark Allen - 2019</p>
